727998f-a.title: Queens: South Road - 54th Street
727998f-a.text:
South Road (old No. 228 to -1), north side, between 154th
(formerly Dubroff Ave.) and 155th Streets(formerly Phraner Ave),
showing several old places in this area.
1922.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.

727834f-a.title: Queens: Queens Boulevard - 54th Street
727834f-a.text:
Queens Bouuleward, north side, east from 54th Street. In
the foreground of views one and three is a section of the
First hreshyterian Cemetery of Newtown. The three views
also show an old structure that has since been modernized
and is distinguishable by its dormmer windows. The homes
seen in there order were the property of H. Geisiing, 9.B,
Mrs. Raymond,and Rapelye in 1873.  We.-1FA
1923
View 2: March 1923
View 3: July 1925.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection
PAY BE REPRODUCED.
